      "name": "LockBit Ransomware Hits Three NHS Hospitals",
      "description": "Three NHS hospitals in England have been struck by LockBit ransomware in what appears to be coordinated attacks over the weekend. Sources inside two of the affected trusts confirmed that IT systems are offline and patient-facing services have been disrupted. Incident response teams have been deployed and the NCSC has been notified. The initial vector is believed to be a phishing campaign exploiting CVE-2024-3094. Patient data may be at risk. The LockBit group is a well-known ransomware-as-a-service operation with previous attacks on healthcare organisations worldwide.",
